Unfortunately, this article conflicts heavily with my understanding of Foundation canon. I haven't seen very many other articles in which the Foundation is concerned with keeping history on its original course specifically. As long as the veil isn't broken and humanity at large is unharmed, there are very few other people who would believe that the Foundation would bother trying to rewrite history like this. The mass amnestization of the entire world population just to put a few civil wars and political scandals in their rightful place, despite there being nothing inherently important to keeping history intact, doesn't fit.







